.TH TILER 1 "December 2025" "tiler 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tiler \- command-line tool for window tiling on X11
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tiler
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tiler
is a powerful command-line tool designed to automatically arrange and resize windows on X11 desktop environments. It provides flexible window tiling capabilities with support for various layout modes, aspect ratio control, and customizable margins.

The tool can tile all visible windows or filter by specific applications. It supports horizontal, vertical, grid, and circular tiling layouts with intelligent multi-display detection.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.

.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-for\-app " " \fINAME\fR
Select windows by application executable name. This option can be repeated to specify multiple applications. The tool matches against the executable basename (e.g., 'firefox', 'kitty').

.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-aspect\-ratio " " \fIW:H\fR
Set aspect ratio for windows (e.g., 16:9, 4:3). Windows will be resized to maintain the specified aspect ratio within their allocated space.

.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-horizontal
Tile windows horizontally in a single row. All windows will have the same height and be arranged side by side.

.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-vertical
Tile windows vertically in a single column. All windows will have the same width and be stacked vertically.

.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-margin " " \fITOP\fR " [" \fIRIGHT\fR " [" \fIBOTTOM\fR " [" \fILEFT\fR "]]]"
Set margins for windows in pixels. Supports 1-4 values:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
1 value: applied to all sides
.IP \(bu 2
2 values: top/bottom, left/right
.IP \(bu 2
3 values: top, left/right, bottom
.IP \(bu 2
4 values: top, right, bottom, left
.RE

.TP
.BR \-\-circular
Tile windows in a circular pattern around the center of the display.

.TP
.BR \-\-circular\-radius " " \fIRADIUS\fR
Set the radius for circular tiling. Can be specified in pixels (e.g., 200) or as a percentage of screen size (e.g., 30%). Default is 30% of the smaller display dimension.

.TP
.BR \-\-circular\-margin " " \fISIZE\fR
Set margin between the circular layout and windows in pixels. This reduces the effective radius by the specified amount.

.TP
.BR \-\-circular\-width " " \fIWIDTH\fR
Set window width for circular layout. Can be specified in pixels (e.g., 150) or as a percentage of screen width (e.g., 20%). Default is calculated based on circle circumference and number of windows.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B tiler
Tile all windows in grid layout (default behavior).

.TP
.B tiler \-H
Tile all windows horizontally in a single row.

.TP
.B tiler \-V
Tile all windows vertically in a single column.

.TP
.B tiler \-\-circular
Tile windows in circular pattern with default settings.

.TP
.B tiler \-a firefox \-a kitty
Tile only Firefox and Kitty windows.

.TP
.B tiler \-r 16:9
Tile all windows with 16:9 aspect ratio.

.TP
.B tiler \-m 10 20 15 5
Tile with custom margins: top=10px, right=20px, bottom=15px, left=5px.

.TP
.B tiler \-a chrome \-H \-m 5
Tile Chrome windows horizontally with 5px margin on all sides.

.TP
.B tiler \-\-circular \-\-circular\-radius 300
Circular tiling with 300px radius.

.TP
.B tiler \-\-circular \-\-circular\-radius 40%
Circular tiling with radius of 40% of screen size.

.TP
.B tiler \-\-circular \-\-circular\-width 200 \-\-circular\-margin 20
Custom circular layout with 200px window width and 20px margin.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Multi-display Support
Automatically detects the current active display and tiles windows only within that display's boundaries. Windows on other displays are ignored.

.TP
.B Application Filtering
Filter windows by executable basename for precise control over which applications to tile.

.TP
.B Aspect Ratio Control
Maintain specific aspect ratios while tiling to preserve window proportions.

.TP
.B Flexible Margins
Support for CSS-style margin specification with 1-4 values.

.TP
.B Circular Tiling
Unique circular tiling mode that arranges windows around the display center with configurable radius, margins, and window sizes.

.TP
.B Smart Window Detection
Automatically excludes minimized windows, system windows, and the tiler process itself.

.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B Python 3.x
Required for script execution.

.TP
.B X11 Environment
Must be running in an X11 desktop session (Linux).

.TP
.B python3-xlib
Python library for X11 interaction.

.TP
.B python3-psutil
Python library for process detection and executable name resolution.

